    <strong>**Privacy Policy for The Cypher Range Vinyl 1990s Underground Hip-Hop Database**</strong>

    <strong>Last Updated</strong>: 10/6/2023

    <strong>Welcome to The Cypher Range Vinyl Underground Hip-Hop Database</strong> ("we," "us," or "our"). This Privacy Policy is designed to inform you about how we collect, use, disclose, and protect your personal information when you use our online database services dedicated to vinyl records within the underground hip-hop genre, known as <strong>"The Cypher Range."</strong> By accessing or using our services, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

    <strong>Information We Collect</strong>
    <strong>Vinyl Record Information</strong>: When you use The Cypher Range, you may voluntarily submit information about underground hip-hop vinyl records, including album names, artists, release years, cover images, and other related data.

    <strong>User-Provided Information</strong>: If you create an account, we may collect personal information such as your name, username, email address, and other contact details.

    <strong>Usage Information</strong>: We may collect information about how you interact with The Cypher Range, including your browsing behavior, search queries, and contributions to the database.

    <strong>Cookies and Similar Technologies</strong>: We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your user experience. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.

    <strong>How We Use Your Information</strong>
    We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

    <strong>Database Operation</strong>: We use your contributed data to operate and maintain The Cypher Range, making it available to other users interested in underground hip-hop vinyl records.

    <strong>User Engagement</strong>: We may use your contact information to send you updates, newsletters, and notifications related to The Cypher Range. You can opt out of these communications at any time.

    <strong>Improvement</strong>: We analyze usage data to enhance The Cypher Range's functionality, improve user experience, and optimize search and recommendation features.

    <strong>Disclosure of Your Information
        We may share your information in the following circumstances
    </strong>:

    <strong>Public Contributions</strong>: Information you voluntarily contribute to The Cypher Range may be publicly accessible to other users interested in underground hip-hop vinyl records.

    <strong>Service Providers</strong>: We may share data with third-party service providers who assist us in operating and maintaining The Cypher Range.

    <strong>Legal Requirements</strong>: We may disclose your information in response to legal requests or when required by law to protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property.

    <strong>Security
        We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or alteration. However, please be aware that no online platform can guarantee absolute security.
    </strong>

    <strong>Your Choices
        You have certain rights regarding your personal information
    </strong>:

    Account Access: You can access and update your personal information through your account settings.

    <strong>Data Removal</strong>: You can request the removal of your account and contributed data by contacting us.

    <strong>Contact Us</strong>
    If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your personal information, please contact us at <strong>TheCypherRange@gmail.com</strong>

    <strong>Changes to this Privacy Policy</strong>
    We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in our <strong>practices, features, or for legal compliance</strong>. The last updated date will be prominently displayed at the beginning of the policy.


